<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[264,1326,284,1190]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,923,949]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Discussion</emphasis>
. The configurations of the vaginal furca resembles that of 
<taxonomicName box="[1148,1315,924,949]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subauratus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1315,924,949]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. subauratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the inward projecting arms however, in the latter species are directed upward; in 
<taxonomicName box="[1203,1323,964,989]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peucon">
<emphasis box="[1203,1323,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. peucon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the projections are straighter. The male genitalia are similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1012,1145,1004,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[1012,1145,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differ primarily in the shorter projections on the gonocoxa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="biology_ecology">
